  "title" : "Create whole path automatically when writing to a new file",
  "body" : "<p>I want to write a new file with the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/io/FileWriter.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>FileWriter</code></a>. I use it like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>FileWriter newJsp = new FileWriter(\"C:\\\\user\\Desktop\\dir1\\dir2\\filename.txt\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Now <code>dir1</code> and <code>dir2</code> currently don't exist. I want Java to create them automatically if they aren't already there. Actually Java should set up the whole file path if not already existing.</p>\n\n<p>How can I achieve this?</p>\n"
}